{"article_id":"4Yis2tEPmThk6efh","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A federal appeals court has unanimously rejected a Trump administration request","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"to allow its travel ban to take effect .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"The three-judge appeals panel declined to overturn a lower court 's order","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"suspending the president 's ban against entry into the United States by refugees and travelers from seven majority-Muslim nations .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The travel ban was put on hold by federal district Judge James L. Robart of Seattle ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"who issued a nationwide restraining order on Feb. 3 .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Robart said","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that the two states","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"challenging the ban ,","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"Washington and Minnesota ,","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"had shown","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"that their residents and universities were harmed by Trump 's action .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"The administration then asked the appeals court for an emergency stay of Robart 's restraining order .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"But the judges dismissed the administration 's request ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that it had to show","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"that it is likely to succeed in the trial court on the merits of its appeal .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"`` [ We ] hold","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"that the Government has not shown a likelihood of success on the merits of its appeal ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"nor has it shown","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"that failure","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"to enter a stay","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"would cause irreparable injury ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"and we therefore deny its emergency motion for a stay , ''","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"wrote the panel .","depth":4},{"id":25,"text":"Trump also spoke briefly with reporters outside his press secretary 's office","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"after the ruling was announced","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"and ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"as reported by Reuters ,","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"called the decision political","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"and predicted","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"the administration would ultimately win .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"The result is a rebuke to the White House .","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"In oral arguments","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"heard on Tuesday ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"the panel vigorously quizzed attorneys both for the administration and for the state of Washington , the lead plaintiff ,","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"which originally filed the suit","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"challenging the travel ban .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"The solicitor general for the state of Washington , Noah Purcell , argued","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"that the travel ban is discriminatory","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"and violates both federal statutes and the U.S. Constitution .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"He told the court","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"that the judiciary 's role is to step in","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"and check the abuses of the executive branch .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"But August Flentje , special counsel to the assistant attorney general , argued","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"that the president has the ultimate authority","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"to protect the national security","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"and that his action in that regard","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"- namely , the travel ban -","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"was unreviewable by the courts .","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"In their ruling , the judges were unequivocal .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"`` There is no precedent","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"to support this claimed unreviewability ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"which runs contrary to the fundamental structure of our democracy , ''","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"the court wrote .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"The judges also said","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"that the administration had also failed to show","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"it would suffer `` irreparable injury ''","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"if its travel ban were not allowed to go back into effect .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Acknowledging the government 's interest","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"in combating terrorism ,","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"the judges nonetheless wrote ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"`` The Government has pointed to no evidence","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"that any alien from any of the countries","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"named in the Order","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"has perpetrated a terrorist attack in the United States .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"Rather than present evidence","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"to explain the need for the Executive Order ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"the Government has taken the position","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"that we must not review the decision at all . ''","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"The states","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"challenging the president 's travel ban","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"won on virtually every issue ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"says Carl Tobias , a law professor at the University of Richmond School of Law .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"`` The order was unanimous .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"The panel found","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"that the states had standing ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"that the executive order was reviewable by the court ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"that the U.S. was not likely to succeed on the merits","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"and that it had not shown","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"that a stay was necessary","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"to avoid irreparable injury , ''","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"said Tobias .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Africa","depth":3},{"id":84,"text":"With Travel Ban On Hold ,","depth":4},{"id":85,"text":"Somali Refugees Take Off For The U.S.","depth":4},{"id":86,"text":"With Travel Ban On Hold ,","depth":5},{"id":87,"text":"Somali Refugees Take Off For The U.S .","depth":5},{"id":88,"text":"Listen ·","depth":5},{"id":89,"text":"2:09","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"2:09","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"In a news conference , Purcell declared victory .","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"`` What we argued","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"is it 's the role of the courts to say what the law is ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"and to serve as a check on the executive branch ,","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"and that 's what the court has done in this opinion , in this excellent opinion , with this well-reasoned , careful , thoughtful opinion","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"that seriously considered all the government 's arguments","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"and rejected them , ''","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"he said .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":197,"left":181,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":123,"right":180,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":115,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":102,"right":114,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":100,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":103,"right":113,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":109,"right":112,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":109,"left":108,"right":12,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":108,"left":6,"right":107,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":107,"left":106,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":106,"left":105,"right":